    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 1st with a lineup headlined by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (67.49) and **Yordan Alvarez** (63.92), representing our most efficient options against today\u2019s opposing arms. Despite a daunting matchup against Gallen, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** earns the top efficiency spot due to an elite dynamic platoon advantage (+14%) that overrides his bottom-of-the-order penalty. Meanwhile, **Yordan Alvarez** continues to provide high-floor production; despite the inherent disadvantage of a left-on-left pairing against Bennett, his elite 0.436 xwOBA makes him an auto-start regardless of context. **Kazuma Okamoto** (63.91) and **Carson Benge** (62.65) also project as strong starts, both benefiting significantly from favorable matchups against pitchers with xERAs above 4.80, allowing them to capitalize on high-upside situations.\n\nOur decision-making process for the utility spot was a tight contest, as **Junior Caminero** (60.63) narrowly edged out fringe candidates who failed to crack the starting nine. The most difficult bench decision involved balancing the volume of **Caleb Durbin** (49.84) against the remaining reserves; while **Caleb Durbin** struggles with a #9 order placement, his base projection and park factors provide just enough stability to keep him active over our deeper bench options. We remain cautious regarding **Chase Meidroth** (57.08) and **Carson Benge** (62.65), as both rely on projected lineup spots that have yet to be confirmed. Should those lineups shift negatively, we risk efficiency drops, though the current data suggests the risk is acceptable given the overall scarcity of elite speed in our current roster configuration. We are also closely monitoring the statuses of **Trea Turner**, **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Colt Keith**, who remain unavailable, keeping our bench depth thin for this slate.",
